		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Sparrow</span></strong>&rsquo;s essay in this issue is from his unpublished book about running for president, which he describes as a cross between Lenin&rsquo;s &ldquo;What Is to Be Done?&rdquo; and the <em>Farmers&rsquo; Almanac</em>. He lives in Phoenicia, New York, with his wife, Violet, and his daughter, Sylvia.</p><a href="/contributors/sparrow" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
